Abdomen . Three exposed tergites, smooth, ventrites microsculpture consisting of points; first ventrite with longitudinal keel, slightly elevate; fourth ventrite with two spine like processes at apex, and fifth ventrite with elliptical area, slightly concave (
Fig. 5
).

Etymology. The name of the species is derived from the Nahuatl word “ Opochtli ” (
Simeon, 1999
), meaning left side, in reference to the curvature toward the left of the median lobe.
